    q: "Why is my U-Line ice maker making small or hollow ice?",
    a: "Small / hollow / underfilled ice on a U-Line built-in ice maker is almost always a water-supply problem — water inlet valve failure or upstream restriction. Three most common causes on the U-BI95B and surrounding U-BI series in LA: (1) Water inlet valve partial failure. The valve opens but doesn't reach full flow — ice cubes form but the mold doesn't fill completely, producing small or hollow cubes. The 2014-2019 U-BI95 production cohort develops a consistent water inlet valve failure around year 5 to 7, and LA hard water is the main accelerant — mineral buildup inside the valve solenoid restricts flow before the part fails outright. Replacement runs $185-$285. (2) Water-line restriction. The 1/4-inch saddle-valve tap (the most common DIY install method) clogs with mineral scale faster than people expect on LA municipal water. A new water-line tap or a full feed-line replacement runs $145-$245. (3) Ice maker module / fill arm misalignment. The fill arm position is calibrated to the mold geometry — a slightly bent or worn fill arm produces consistently undersize cubes. Diagnostic identifies which on-site. Hard water mineral buildup is the single most common root cause of U-Line ice maker symptoms across our LA service mix."
